- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing social networks and their communication patterns. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper mentions using novel network metrics to characterize network configurations. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper deals with the impact of network structure on the diversity and novelty of information being communicated, which has societal implications.
